docs.lead_paragraph: In a study comparing births from 1959 to 1966 with those from 2002 to 2008, scientists conclude that the reason for longer labor may be changes in obstetric practices.

headline.seo: Childbirth Takes Longer Than 50 Years Ago, Study Says
headline.main: Childbirth Is Taking Longer, Study Finds
headline.print_headline: Childbirth Is Taking Longer, Study Finds

docs.abstract: Study published in the American Journal of Obstetrics and Gynecology finds that women spend much more time in labor than they did 50 years ago, and one reason may be that obstetric practices have changed.
docs.snippet: In a study comparing births from 1959 to 1966 with those from 2002 to 2008, scientists conclude that the reason for longer labor may be changes in obstetric practices.
